{"word":"σταθμάω","slug":"σταθμάω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>σταθμάω</b></el> <el>(σταθμάω,) ( φυτ. <el>-ήσω</el>) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:στάθμη'><el>στάθμη</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to measure by rule</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>: —<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, with <a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>mid.</a> <el>-ήσομαι</el>, <i>to be measured, estimated</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>as <a href='S:Deponent Verb, i.e. a Verb of Middle or Passive form with Active sense'>Dep.</a> (<a href='S:vide'>v.</a> <a href='S:σταθμόω'><el>σταθμόω</el></a>), <i>to estimate</i> distance or size, without actual measurement, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>: <a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>to estimate</i> one thing <i>by</i> another, <el>τί τινι</el> <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>; <a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> <i>to conjecture</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to attach weight to</i> a thing, <i>value</i> it, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}